    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-10T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-10T12:00:00-05:00" n="1058"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1058">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/4078: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sparks</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-10T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 10, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>176. At the request of President Vincent the Cabinet resigned this morning.</p>
                <p>The Minister of Finance informs the Fiscal Representative that the crisis
                    resulted from a disagreement over the reply which President Vincent made
                    yesterday to the Department’s telegram No. 160, October 5, 1 p.m., the Cabinet
                    having taken the position that something constructive must be done in view of
                    the unalterable conviction of the American Government on communal revenues.
                    President Vincent is reported to have reproached the Cabinet for even suggesting
                    an agreement since they knew that the communal funds are absolutely necessary
                    for the forthcoming elections. He was particularly bitter against Laleau and
                    criticized his actions at Habana and elsewhere.</p>
                <p>The Minister of Finance is reported to have added that the drastic salary
                    reductions cannot work and that the Government employees are dissatisfied but
                    that the President does not understand.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sparks</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
